<DOCNO> XIE19970924.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Sign Tax Pact With Mauritius </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet today agreed
to sign with Mauritius an agreement on the avoidance of double
taxation, the Thai Government House said here today.
</P>
<P>
The pact will be signed when the finance minister of Mauritius
visits Thailand on October 1 this year, the government house said
in a press release.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the international air services between the
two sides will be exempted from taxation and the tax for
international maritime services between them will be cut by half.
</P>
<P>
The pact will promote the movement of capital fund and
technology know-how between the countries, the Thai Government
House noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
