<HEADLINE> Kim Young Sam Congratulates Jiang's Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- President of South Korea's
ruling New Korea Party Kim Young Sam has sent a congratulatory
message on the success of the 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), and on Jiang Zemin's re-election
as CPC Central Committee general secretary.
</P>
<P>
In the message, Kim said that the Congress has set the
direction for the development of China in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes that under Jiang's leadership, China will
continue the reform and opening up policy and the cause of
building a socialist and modern China with stability.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his wish to promote relations and cooperation
between his party and the CPC, and the two nations. 
</P>
