<HEADLINE> German Reinsurer to Buy 20 Pct Stake in Italy's Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Germany's reinsurance giant
Muenchner Rueck today announced plans to buy a 20 percent stake in
Italy's second-largest reinsurance company Reale Ri by the end of
this year.
</P>
<P>
Under a letter of intent signed with Reale Ri's parent company
Reale Mutua, which has 90 percent ownership of Reale Ri, Muenchner
Rueck was planning to spend 550 billion lires (about 315 million
U.S. dollars) for the deal.
</P>
<P>
As the world's largest reinsurance company, Muenchner Rueck
also wanted to further expand its stake in Reale Ri in the coming
years, a spokesman of the company said. He did not rule out the
possibility that his company would eventually take over a majority
ownership of the Italian firm.
</P>
<P>
By buying into Reale Ri, Muenchner Rueck would expand its
operations in Italy to include life, health, and private house
insurance items, the spokesman added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
