<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Xinhua Macao Branch Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng said here
today that the Chinese Government is confident that Macao will
achieve smooth transition and successful handover, and maintain
long-term stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark while meeting with Xinhua Macao Branch
officials.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong has returned smoothly to the motherland
and Macao will return to the motherland next.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the return of Macao has some favorable
conditions, but still needs hard work. "On the whole, there are
more opportunities than challenges," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Premier asked Xinhua Macao Branch to continue its efforts
to unite and rely on Macao residents in doing all kinds of work
related to Macao's smooth return, under the leadership of the
Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party with Jiang Zemin
at the core.  
</P>
</TEXT>
