<HEADLINE> Ugandan Party Congratulates Jiang on Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan National Resistance
Movement (NRM) extended its congratulations to Jiang Zemin on his
re-election as general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
B. Chango Machyo W'obanda, NRM deputy commissar, said in his
message that they "salute the wise leadership of the CPC and the
Chinese people for the enormous efforts made to develop the
country and emancipate the masses."
</P>
<P>
"China has historical links with the struggle that liberated
Africa, still inspires many of our countries in the south,
especially with regard to the independent path of development,"
Machyo W'obanda said.
</P>
<P>
The commissar said Uganda wishes China total success in
implementing the resolutions of the 15th National Congress of the
CPC and continued all round development.
</P>
<P>
He said Uganda also wishes to enhance further its friendly
cooperation with China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
