<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets Czech Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier
and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen talked over cooperation with his
Czech counterpart, Josef Zielenic.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that there have been prolonged friendly and
cooperative relations between the Chinese and Czech peoples. The
bilateral economic and trade relations have advanced further in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
He said that the 15th National Congress of the Chinese
Communist Party outlined the targets for the country in reforms,
opening up and economic construction for the years ahead. And
China resumed its exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July
1. Both events will be of great historic importance for China's
development, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Qian said he believes that Chinese and Czech economic and trade
cooperation will show a great prospect.
</P>
<P>
Zielenic, Czech deputy prime minister and foreign minister,
said that Czech and China traditionally have friendly and close
relations. The Czech government has regarded the development of
its relations with China as a priority goal in its external
policy. It values highly a good economic and trade cooperation and
is willing to further the mutually beneficial cooperation with the
Chinese, according to the Czech leader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
