<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belarus Enjoys Economy Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Belarus has ended its
economic slump with an 11 percent increase in gross domestic
production (GDP) for the first half of the year, said a news
release distributed by today the Belarussian presidential press
secretary.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, Belarus has experienced a consecutive
increase in GDP since March, 1996. The industrial production for
the first six months this year gained 13.9 percent compared with
the same period of last year, while agricultural production was up
4.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The release was distributed here during Belarussian President
Lukashenko's visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
