<HEADLINE> Pak President Calls for Muslim Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Farooq
Leghari today stressed the need for meaningful cooperation among
Muslim countries in the field of science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Meeting a visiting 10-member Egyptian parliamentary delegation
here earlier in the day, Leghari said there exists great potential
for economic cooperation between Pakistan and Egypt, according to
official sources.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the confidence that the visit of the delegation
would prove a milestone in strengthening relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Leghari said the peoples of Pakistan and Arab
countries are emotionally attached to each other and hence
Pakistan has been supporting their cause.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan supports Arab consensus on the issue of Palestine,
Leghari said.
</P>
<P>
On his country's relations with India, Leghari said Pakistan
wants to resolve all outstanding issues with India including the
core issue of Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the Egyptian guests noted that Pakistan and
Egypt have always enjoyed excellent relations.  
