<HEADLINE> Iran Manufactures First Jet Fighter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Iran said today that it has
manufactured its first jet fighter which features assault ability
upon ground targets, Iran's official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Iranian army Chief of Staff Ali Shahbazi was quoted as saying
that Iran has made its first jet fighter "Ouj", which will be
tested in a mission in Zulfaqar military exercises near Qom, 150
kilometers south of Iran's capital Tehran.
</P>
<P>
He said the Iranian air force has set up an assembling line of
the jet fighter thanks to the special attention paid by Iran's
Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
Shahbazi said that Iran's three services are ready to cooperate
with the neighboring states in maintaining peace and security in
the region.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ali Akbar Shouqi, chancellor of Shahid Sattari
University affiliated to Iran's air force, said that the
university is ready to enroll students from Muslim and other
friendly countries in the region. 
</P>
