U.N. General Assembly, Lebanese official National News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
At next Monday's session, Boueiz will address the assembly
about Lebanese stance toward the Middle East peace negotiations
which have been suspended since Israel began construction of a
Jewish settlement in Arab East Jerusalem in March, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
Boueiz will mention in his speech the Israeli aggression of
Lebanon's south and western Bekaa area, which has caused
material and human losses.
</P>
