Meanwhile, he will urge Israel to implement the
U.N. resolution 425 which demands Israel withdraw from Lebanon
unconditionally, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The issue of Lebanese detainees held in jails in Israel or in
Israeli camps in south Lebanon occupied by Israel will also be
raised in Boueiz's speech.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in New York, the foreign minister will meet
his counterparts from 15 countries. But the report did not say if
Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy will be included.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright has
announced in her maiden trip to the Middle East that she had made
arrangements for the meeting in Washington next week between
Israeli and Palestinian officials and she will meet senior
officials of Israel, Syria and Lebanon separately. 
