<HEADLINE> 4 Suicide Bombers in Jerusalem Bombings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister's
Office announced here this evening that four of the five suicide
bombers in the Jerusalem bombings have been identified.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said that with the help of the Biology
Laboratory of Forensic Medical Institute of Israel, Israeli
security services have identified four of the five suicide
bombers who conducted the bombings in Jerusalem on July 30 and
September 4.
</P>
<P>
The two bombing attacks claimed 25 lives, including the five
bombers.
</P>
<P>
The security services' evaluation is based on intelligence
data and DNA tests, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
It gave three bombers' names as Mahmoud Ahmad Jarara, Mahmoud
Asad Zoualha and Ali Mahmoud Yassin. The fourth Bomber, named as
Yosef Ahmad shouli, is still being checked.
</P>
<P>
All the four suicide bombers were residents of the village
Aziraa Shamaliya near Nablus in West Bank, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
The four were wanted by Israel General Security Services for
their involvement in the shooting attack at vehicles of Israel
Defense Forces near Nablus in 1996, during which an Israeli army
doctor and a soldier were wounded, it said.
</P>
<P>
They were arrested by the Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) in 1996, but escaped from prison in Nablus the same year.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said that the four were included in the list
of 88 Hamas and Islamic Jihad (two Palestinian Islamic
resistance groups) activists whose arrests were requested by
Israel. 
</P>
