<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10 Qualified for Cameroon's Presidential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Ten candidates have been
selected today for the October 12 presidential elections in
Cameroon.
</P>
<P>
The official list of the candidates has been published in
Yaounde by the Ministry of Territorial Administration after five
days screening of the candidates' files.
</P>
<P>
According to the officials in the ministry, 17 candidates
handed in their files to the ministry for scrutiny, only 10 have
been retained.
</P>
<P>
Among the 10 candidates qualified for the upcoming
presidential elections include President Paul Biya of the
Cameroon People's Democratic Movement, Albert Dzongang of
the Democracy and Progress Party, Samuel Eboua of the
Movement for Democracy and Progress, and Gustave Essaka of the
Integral Democracy in Cameroon.
</P>
<P>
The seven others were rejected for lack of complete documents.
</P>
<P>
Officials in the Ministry of Territorial Administration
disclosed that Some of the files did not contain a copy of the
candidate's birth certificate, while others did not have
certificates of nationality.
</P>
<P>
Some files did not contain the certificates of 1.5 million CFA
Francs deposited into the public treasury as stipulated by the
law and some files lacked of his party's investiture.
</P>
<P>
According to the officials in the ministry, the candidates
whose files have been rejected have 72 hours from the day of the
publication of the list to take their cases to the supreme court,
which has to make known its verdict at most three days following
the launching of their appeal.  
</P>
</TEXT>
