<HEADLINE> International Panda Festival Opens In Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- An international panda
festival opened today in Chengdu, the capital of China's Sichuan
province to show the country's determination to protect environment.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the five-day event
is 'Life-Environment-Development' It is sponsored by the Forestry,
Construction, and Culture ministries and the Information Office of
the State Council, Environmental Protection Bureau, China National
Tourism Administration, and the local government.
</P>
<P>
New methods of panda protection and state-level ecology
programs will be announced at the event and cultural activities
and performances will be provided.
</P>
<P>
An international seminar on environmental protection and urban
development for the 21st century will also be held. It has
attracted representatives of international organizations like the
UN Environment Program and World Wildlife Fund.
</P>
<P>
Participants will discuss improving wildlife protection
policies and breeding, habitats, and migration habits.
</P>
<P>
Because of the deterioration of the environment and the
degeneration of animal's reproductive capacity, the number of
pandas, an animal that is found in Sichuan, Shaanxi and Gansu
Provinces only, has dropped dramatically to just over
1,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
