talks. The two leaders did say they had established "progress" for
discussing American complaints.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal
</P>
<P>
-- Toyota plans to build at least one more assembly plant in
North America and Honda is scouting sites for a fourth plant in
the U.S. or Canada. The moves represent a heightened
aggressiveness toward the Big Three by the Japanese auto makers.
</P>
<P>
-- Shell Oil Co., making an aggressive move into natural-gas
marketing, agreed to acquire Tejas Gas Corp. for about 1.45
billion U.S. dollars in cash, or 61.50 dollars a share. The
agreement represents one of the first attempts by a major oil
company to tackle the competitive natural-gas marketing business
alone. 
</P>
