<HEADLINE> Central Government Departments Study Party Congress Documents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Central Government
departments agree that taking Deng Xiaoping Theory as the
guiding ideology, an important part of the 15th National Congress
of the Communist Party of China (CPC), is the will and common
aspiration of the Party and the people.
</P>
<P>
A campaign to study the Congress documents has been started in
central government departments. At the General Office of the State
Council and the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Party members and
officials say that the theory about the primary stage of socialism
is the cornerstone of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
The reform of state enterprises remains a major topic among
departments officials, who say that General Secretary Jiang
Zemin's report at the Congress states that public ownership can
and should find expression in diverse forms, and that the
distribution system allows and encourages the use of capital and
technology to become involved income distribution.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the State Science and Technology Commission and
Education Commission say that they were encouraged by Jiang's
emphasis on invigorating China by means of science and
education, something that clearly defines the status of education
as a developmental priority.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the Supreme People's Court, the Supreme People's
Procuratorate, the Ministry of Public Security, and the Ministry
of Justice expressed a determination to help introduce a socialist
legal system, to govern the country according to the law, and to
make a contribution to China's stability. 
</P>
