<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Leader Meets With Brazilian Naval Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Vice-chairman of the
Central Military Commission (CMC) Zhang Wannian, meeting today
with Mauro Cesar Rodrigues Pereira, Brazil's Minister of the Navy,
said that Sino-Brazilian relations have developed smoothly in
recent years and that the China appreciates the forging a
strategic partnership between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that the Chinese side is ready to work with the
Brazilian side to push long-term, stable and mutually-beneficial
bilateral relations into the next century.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the two countries' armed forces will
develop friendly relations in a steady and sustained way to
contribute to regional and world peace.
