<HEADLINE> Chinese General Meets US Army Chief Of Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Gen. Chi Haotian, China's
vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and defense
minister, meeting today with Gen. Dennis Reimer, US Army Chief of
Staff, said that the upcoming Sino-US summit in Washington will be
the focus of the world.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin's visit, scheduled for October, is an
important event in Sino-US relations, Chi said, noting that
 the meeting between President Jiang and President Bill Clinton
last November brought Sino-US ties to a new development period.
</P>
<P>
The US is the largest developed country and China the largest
developing one, the two are playing an important role in the world
and should make every effort to bring stable and healthy Sino-US
ties into the next century, Chi stressed. This is in the interest
of the people of both countries, and will help safeguard peace and
stability in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
With the development of Sino-US ties, relations between the two
armed forces have become stronger, he said, adding that he
believes that Reimer's visit will contribute to the further
development of relations.
</P>
<P>
Reimer said that the visit will help him to forge closer ties
with his Chinese counterpart and better understand China.
</P>
<P>
He had a frank and in-depth discussion with Kui Fulin, deputy
Chief of General Staff of the PLA, yesterday, and that the two
sides agreed that there is more in common than the differences
between them.
</P>
<P>
The two armed forces should continue the exchange of visits, he
said, to enhance understanding and build on this common
ground. The two sides should make more efforts to help make the
world safer, he added.  
