<HEADLINE> Four Killed, 14 injured in Road Accidents in S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed
and 14 others injured in two separate road accidents in the
central Free State province, South African Press Association
(SAPA) reported today.
</P>
<P>
Two policemen were killed this morning in Bloemfontein when a
petrol tanker allegedly jumped a red light and collided with a
police vehicle.
</P>
<P>
Six other police officers and a pedestrian were injured in the
accident.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the tanker has been arrested and could face
charges of culpable homicide, SAPA quoted Free State police
spokeswoman Mientjte Bruwer as saying.
</P>
<P>
In another accident, two film crew members were killed and
seven of their colleagues injured when their minibus collided
with a passenger bus on the Harrismith-Qwa-Qwa road Tuesday
evening.
</P>
<P>
The collision occurred when the bus made a U-turn on the road,
SAPA said. The bus was not carrying any passengers and the driver
was unhurt.
</P>
<P>
The crew members, from the Mmula Productions in Gauteng, were
filming in the Harrismith area in the eastern part of the Free
State province. 
</P>
