<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Guidelines for Japan-US Defense Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Defense cooperation between
Japan and the United States, a bilateral arrangement formed under
certain historical circumstances, should be strictly limited
within the bilateral scope in order to prevent arousing unrest
amongst Asian nations and bringing unnecessarily complicated
factors to the regional security situation.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang made the
remarks today in response to a question raised by Xinhua
concerning the recently introduced guidelines for Japan-US defense
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the practice of strengthening military
alliance and expanding military cooperation run counter to the
trends in the situation in the Asia-Pacific Region which is
witnessing relative political stability, sustained economic growth
and active security dialogue," said Shen.
</P>
<P>
"We have consistently urged Japan and the United States to
proceed cautiously concerning the defense cooperation issue,
including reviewing guidelines, practicing restraint rather than
expanding the scope of cooperation under their alliance, and
refraining from actions which might in any way arouse concern
amongst neighboring countries."
</P>
<P>
Shen also pointed out that due to historical reasons,
orientation of Japan's defense policy has always been a very
sensitive issue to neighboring Asian nations. Shen expressed the
hope that Japan draws lessons from history and firmly follow the
path of peaceful development.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that an important reason China is concerned about
the guidelines for Japan-US defense cooperation rests with its
relationship to the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
As everyone knows, Taiwan is an inseparable part of China. "The
Chinese government and people will never accept violations of or
interference in China's sovereignty by either directly or
indirectly including the Taiwan straits in the scope of Japan-US
defense cooperation, Shen said.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that both Japan and the US will honor their
commitments to China concerning the Taiwan issue, respect the
solemn stance of the Chinese side in this regard, and refrain from
doing anything which will in any way harm China's interests or
hurt the feelings of the Chinese people."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
