and runners-up advancing the knockout phase of a tournament first
staged 40 years ago in Khartoum.
</P>
<P>
Ouagadougou hosts two groups, one of which will include Burkina
Faso, while South Africa are expected to play their three
first-round matches in Bobo-Dioulasso, a town 320km south-west of
the capital. 
