<HEADLINE> Aggression In Women Due To Elevated Testosterone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Women who are aggressive may
be suffering from elevated testosterone levels, a recent American
study on female prisoners has found, the Daily Telegraph reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The results of the study, carried out by scientists from
the Georgia State University on 90 female prisoners, show that those
whose crimes involved violence have higher testosterone levels
than the others,
</P>
<P>
High testosterone level is also present in women who are
aggressively domineering.
</P>
<P>
The study finds that the aggression dwindled with age as the
testosterone levels fall. But older inmates, who still have high
levels of the hormone, are just as aggressive or dominant as when
younger. 
</P>
</TEXT>
