<HEADLINE> WB Says Happy with China's Agenda of Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The agenda of reforms set
by the just-concluded 15th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China is very important for the World Bank to provide
advice to its partners in East Asia, a senior bank official said
today.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Michel Severino, the bank's regional vice-president for
East Asia and Pacific, said the World Bank is especially happy
with the move of the congress to reform China's state-owned
enterprises and its financial sector, which will be of good help
for East Asian countries to make a success of their reforms which
the bank has long advocated.
</P>
