over the past week at a press briefing here, Severino said that
another issue on top of the agenda of the seminars is the
situation in Southeast Asia, on which much of the discussions was
focused.
</P>
<P>
He said the World Bank will actively participate in the efforts
of Southeast Asian countries and strengthen its supply to its
clients there.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank will also strengthen its activity in Southeast
Asia to probe the causes of the financial crisis which has swept
the region in the past months, he said.  
