<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ma Man Kei on 15th CPC National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Ma Man Kei, vice-chairman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), recently noted that the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) drafted
strategic plans for China's development well into the next century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin's report contained an explicit explanation of the
Macao question and greatly increased the confidence of the
majority of Macao compatriots on their future, said Ma, who also
serves as president of the Chinese General Chamber of Commerce of
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Ma, 77, who attended the 15th CPC National Congress as a
special nonvoting delegate, said it was an honor for him and he is
excited about having been present at such a significant meeting.
</P>
<P>
China's comprehensive national strength has increased rapidly
over the past decade and the living standards of the people have
improved significantly under the direction of Deng Xiaoping
Theory, said Ma.
</P>
<P>
The 15th Party Congress defined Deng Xiaoping Theory as a great
banner, said Ma, adding that the move complies totally with the
requirements of the times and the will of the people.
</P>
<P>
Ma also noted that the 15th Party Congress has made
arrangements for political reform, building a democratic legal
system and cultural progress. He said that strengthening the rule
of the country according to law and ensuring ethical and cultural
progress represented a major achievement of the congress.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's report emphasized that the Party will never allow
corrupt people to hide in the party. Jiang also noted that
anti-corruption represents a decisive political struggle related
to the life and death of the Party and the country.
</P>
<P>
Ma, a resident of Macao since the 1940s, said the 15th CPC
National Congress has greatly bolstered Macao's social stability,
economic development and the forthcoming smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
He said the "one country, two systems" principle advanced by
Deng Xiaoping has been implemented smoothly in Hong Kong, a fact
which shows that the Communist Party of China and the Central
Government will keep their promises.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin noted that Macao's return to the embrace of the
motherland in 1999 will be yet another significant event for the
Chinese nation, said the confident Ma, adding that Jiang's report
portends "bright prospects for Macao".  
</P>
</TEXT>
