<HEADLINE> WFP Delegation Arrives in Xining </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A 13-member delegation from
the Rome-based UN World Food Program (WFP) arrived today in
Xining, the capital of Qinghai Province, on the first leg of a
northwest China visit.
</P>
<P>
They are scheduled to spend a week visiting WFP-aided projects
in Qinghai and Gansu provinces and will talk with local government
officials.
</P>
<P>
Officials from China's agriculture and finance ministries, and
the State Council Leading Group of Poverty Alleviation and
Development have joined the tour.
</P>
<P>
According to Ministry of Agriculture officials, China now has
58 million people below the poverty line, living mainly in rocky
areas with very harsh natural conditions.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, China has tried hard to use its own resources
to fight poverty, but has also sought assistance and co-operation
from international organizations to help finance its
poverty-eradication program. 
</P>
