<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Little Changed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
little changed today in Sydney, after being beaten back off the
day's highs by selling of the currency against the Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The local unit finished at 71.98 U.S. cents, compared to 72.02
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Stuart Moore, foreign exchange trading manager with St. George
Bank, cited options related buying out of Singapore at 71.90 U.S.
cents, and Japanese and other offshore-related selling when the
unit moved toward 72.20. The Australian dollar peaked today at
72.15 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar fell against the yen in sympathy with a
weaker U.S. dollar/yen rate.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 86.50 yen, down from 87.59, and
at 1.2858 marks from 1.2880 marks. 
</P>
