<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fresh Community Clash Kills 10 in S. Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 persons have been
feared dead in a new wave of bloody clash between two rival
communities in south Nigeria's Osun state since Monday, the New
Nigerian reported today.
</P>
<P>
The renewed clash between the people of Ile-Ife and Modakeke
communities, which started early Monday, also resulted in the
burning down of about eight houses with an unidentified number of
people injured, the official newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The two communities went into hostilities last month over the
relocation of the local government headquarters from Modakeke to
Oke-Ogbo in Ile-Ife.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of people were killed while more than 100 others were
injured, with houses, vehicles and other properties set on fire.
Anti-riot police has since been deployed and the situation began
to calm down.
</P>
<P>
But the fragile peace in the area for the past weeks was
broken after the anti-riot police was sent to a neighboring area
to quell another riot triggered off by the reinstatement of a
local government chairman formerly removed by the election
tribunal.
</P>
<P>
The people of Ile-Ife and Modakeke communities reportedly
launched attacks on each other on Monday morning following the
re-deployment of the police, and the clash later turned into a
free for all fight.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper, the August clash could better be
described as a child play to the present fracas as youths from
both sides were more militant in their approach this time around.
They often engaged themselves in face to face battle using both
modern weapons and "juju".
</P>
<P>
The state police commissioner has moved into the "war zone"
with his men to restore peace to the area, while armed soldiers
have also been sent there.
</P>
<P>
However, the situation in the area still remained unchanged as
youths from the two communities have vowed not to give up the
fight, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
