<HEADLINE> Investment Talks, Commodities Fair Open in Chengdu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Southwest China
Investment talks and Commodities Fair opened today in Chengdu,
capital of Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
Delegations from 11 foreign countries, including the United
States, France, Germany, Japan and Singapore, as well as from
eight Chinese cities, such as Ningbo, Qingdao and Jinan are
attending the fair sponsored by Yunnan, Guizhou and Sichuan
provinces, the Guangxi Zhuang and Tibet autonomous regions and
Chongqing Municipality.
</P>
<P>
The fair will feature more than 2,000 brand and new products
made locally, including automobiles and motorcycles, and a number
of projects open for foreign investors. New preferential policies
for investment will be also announced during the fair.  
</P>
</TEXT>
