<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PAP Project Reciprocate in Uganda Impressive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Poverty Alleviation Project
(PAP) in the first 22 districts in Uganda received reciprocate
more than 1.1 billion Uganda Shillings (some 1.1 million U.S.
Dollars), ''the New Vision'' reported today.
</P>
<P>
The sum of the African Development Bank (ADB) funded program
represents 74 percent recovery rate, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Wilson Wamatsembe, the national project analyst, told the
paper that most beneficiaries have used their loans fruitfully
and now they are paying back.
</P>
<P>
But still, there are some districts where the PAP project
performance is undesired due to the security reason. He gave
Bundibugyo district in the west as an example where the recovery
rate is only 57 percent.
</P>
<P>
Richard Wanderema, the Bundibugyo project officer, explained
that some local population left their homes since the Allied
Democratic Forces rebels invaded into the district.
</P>
<P>
The soft loans provided by PAP project have been utilized by
local people in small scale business such as farming, bakery and
music/video production activities.
</P>
<P>
PAP project was started three years ago in 22 districts and
now it is set to cover whole the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
