<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Inflation Down to 1.8 Percent in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Germany's annual rate of
inflation has fallen back to 1.8 percent in September from
August's reading of 2 percent, preliminary figures released
today by the German Federal Statistics Office showed.
</P>
<P>
When measured against the previous month, consumer prices fell
0.3 percent in September after rising 0.2 percent in August.
</P>
<P>
The figures were based on consumer prices registered in four of
the most populous western German states, the statistics office
said. The final data would be published in mid-October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
