<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Alerts of Ukrainian Ships in S. Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Defense Headquarters
confirmed today that two Ukrainian ships have been seen on the
territorial waters of Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
But a defense spokesman said the mission of the ships,
reportedly to be in the troubled country since last week, is
unknown so far.
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leone is now under the economic embargo endorsed by its
west African neighbors who want the military junta to return
power to the legitimate government it overthrew in the May 25
coup.
</P>
<P>
The west African peace-keeping force known as ECOMOG is there
to enforce the embargo. ECOMOG has warned that it will attack any
vessels and aircraft trying to enter Sierra Leone without the
force's approval.
</P>
<P>
Lt. Col. Sam Tella, the defense spokesman, told Xinhua this
morning that investigations are underway to find out the
objective of the Ukrainian ships.
</P>
<P>
However, he ensured that "as soon as the result of the probe
is out, we will definitely let the public know".
</P>
<P>
As for the reported presence of a British warship in Sierra
Leone, the spokesman said he has no fears because Britain has
been supportive on the issue of reinstating democracy in Sierra
Leone.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman reiterated that ECOMOG troops, mainly Nigerian
soldiers, are not fighting Sierra Leone but only out to enforce
the economic sanctions imposed by west African leaders to force
the junta out.
</P>
<P>
He rejected reports of ECOMOG bombardment of power plants and
hospitals, saying that they are lies "being perpetrated by the
junta as part of its propaganda against the Nigerian government
and ECOMOG". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
