<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined on
the Singapore market after rising in the last two days, as the
benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index fell by 15.59 points to
close at 1,900.51 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 211.58 million units, worth
465.81 million Singapore dollars (about 306.45 million U.S.
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 262 to 78, while 269
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Rekapac was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 15.17 million units. It was followed by RHB Cap
Warrant99 which had 15.16 million units traded. MBf Capital was
next with 11.83 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 60 cents to end at 34 Singapore dollars.
Jurong Shipyard gained 45 cents to finish at seven Singapore
dollars, while the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign
increased by 40 cents to close at 15.4 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign was the
biggest loser as it declined by 70 cents to close at 10.4
Singapore dollars. The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign fell
by 50 cents to end at 21.1 Singapore dollars, and WTK was 40 cents
lower finishing at 4.6 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
