<HEADLINE> Seoul High Court Upholds Sentence for Hanbo Owner Chung Tae-soo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chung was convicted by the Seoul District Court of embezzling 191.1
billion won (about 210 million USD) of company funds and giving bribes
totaling 3.25 billion won to politicians and bankers.
</P>
<P>
As return, Chung was able to get about 4.5 trillion-won loans from
the banks and other preferences from the administration as well as the
Nation Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors had demanded a 20-year sentence for Chung in the first
trial.
</P>
<P>
Other nine defendants involving in the scam, including four ruling
and opposition lawmakers, three bank heads, a former Home Minister and
Chung's son, were also sentenced to three-six year prison terms and
fines in respect of the amount they received.
</P>
<P>
In announcing the sentences, the presiding judge lamented that
Hanbo's owner Chung, whose unhealthy and immoral management had caused
crisis in society and the national economy, should be sternly
punished. 
</P>
</TEXT>
