<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Recidivism Rate Low in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The recidivism rate among
imprisoned criminals in China has been kept under eight percent
during the past 30 years -- the lowest of any country in the
world.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Ministry of Justice attribute this to the
modern and civilized methods used in Chinese prisons and
reform-through-labor institutes to educate inmates.
</P>
<P>
The ministry launched a project to build modern and civilized
prisons and reform institutes in January 1994. Five prisons and five
reform institutes have been cited as outstanding examples.
</P>
<P>
The project has proved effective in promoting the scientific
management system, improving the re-education methods in prisons
and reform institutes, and as a result reducing recidivism.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
