<HEADLINE> Campaign Against Rinderpest Launched in E. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) has embarked on a campaign to eradicate cattle's
rinderpest in the east African region, according to an East
African Standard report today.
</P>
<P>
The daily newspaper said that the vaccination campaign in
Uganda, Tanzania and Kenya is being undertaken by OAU's
Inter-African Bureau for Animal Resources.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted the Pan African Rinderpest Campaign as saying
in a press release that the vaccination had targeted cattle from
remote parts and areas covering international boundaries.
</P>
<P>
The areas to be covered in the campaign include the zone south
of the Central Railway line and west of Tabora-Mwanza railway
line in Tanzania and the zone of Kenya and Tanzania south of the
Mombasa-Kisumu railway line.
</P>
<P>
Vaccination was preceded by intensive awareness campaigns for
livestock owners and the general public, the paper pointed out.
</P>
