<HEADLINE> S. Africa Not to Bid for 2006 C'wealth Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- South Africa will not
bid for the 2006 Commonwealth Games, Ministry of Sport and
Recreation Director-general Mthobi Tyamzashe has said here.
</P>
<P>
The official, who chairs the Commonwealth Games Association of
South Africa, admitted Tuesday that his country has learned a big
lesson after Cape Town's failed bid for the 2004 Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
He said a forum to evaluate any further bids for major sport
events will be established in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The association took a decision to bring together all the role
of players and establish a forum where they can decide what they
will bid for in the next 10 years, the official told the media.
</P>
<P>
With soccer planning a bid for 2006 World Cup and a possible
bid for the 2008 Olympics in the offing, Tyamzashe said he is
concerned that South Africa will be more realistic when it comes
to hosting major events. 
</P>
