<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Arrives in Alma Ata </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
arrived here today for a one-day working visit at the invitation
of Kazakh President Nursultan Abishevich Nazarbayev.
</P>
<P>
Li is scheduled to hold talks with Nazarbayev later
today. China and Kazakhstan are expected to sign an oil contract
during Li's visit.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier were greeted at the airport by acting Prime
Minister Akhmetzhan Smagulovoch Esimov, Deputy Prime Minister and
Minister of Economy and Trade Umirzak Estaevich Shukeev and other
government officials.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing, who arrived here earlier from
Beijing, also greeted Li Peng at the airport.
</P>
<P>
Li just attended the opening session of the annual meetings of
the World Bank Groups and the International Monetary Fund in Hong
Kong and flew here earlier today after a transition stop in South
China's Zhuhai. 
</P>
