<HEADLINE> Thai House Starts Debate on No-Confidence Motion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's House of
Representatives today opened the debate on the no-confidence
motion launched by the opposition against Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh and his six-party coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Chart Chai party leader Banharn Silpa-Archa cited a large
quantity of economic figures to attack Chavalit and the ruling
coalition's failure in managing the country, especially the
economy.
</P>
<P>
The former prime minister accused the ruling coalition of
bringing the country's economy to the edge of collapse and adding
pains to the people.
</P>
<P>
Opposition leader Chuan Leekpai and other opposition parliament
members also gave speeches during the debate.
</P>
<P>
Chavalit counter-attacked the opposition's accusations through
citing the government's measures and policies aimed at tackling
the country's economic problems.
</P>
<P>
He also explained the current economic situation in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The debate was presided by President Wan Muhamad Nor Matha of
the Thai National Assembly. It is expected to continue on
Thursday.  
</P>
