<HEADLINE> Stable North China Steel Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The steel industry in
north China's Hebei Province has enjoyed a steady growth and the
sector has emerged as a pillar industry.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year alone, the province's steel
manufacturers produced 4.94 million tons of steel, 5.96 million
tons of pig iron and 3.32 million tons of rolled steel, up ten
percent respectively on last year's same period. In addition, the
figures ranked Hebei third, second and fourth nationally in terms
of the respective categories.
</P>
<P>
Hebei's metallurgical sector has witnessed a dramatic rise in
fixes assest investment, with the sector completing 120 major
projects at a cost of tens million yuan each over the past five
years.
</P>
<P>
The Tangshan and Handan iron and steel corporations have become
the country's two major iron and steel complexes, each with an
annual production of two million tons of pig iron, steel and
rolled steel.  
</P>
</TEXT>
