<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal Has Most Maternal Deaths in South Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Nepal accounts for the most
maternal deaths among the South Asian countries with 515 deaths
among every 100,000 women every year, the official RSS news agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
These women die from unprotected abortion and infection caused
hereby, the agency quoted the Family Planning Association of Nepal
(FPAN) as saying.
</P>
<P>
Poverty, illiteracy, lack of public awareness and social
pressure are the main reasons behind illegal abortion practices,
the FPAN said.
</P>
<P>
Almost 71 percent women in Nepal are ignorant that most
maternal deaths are caused by unsafe abortions, the FPAN said.
</P>
<P>
Nepal bans abortion and 75 percent of women behind bars were
jailed for undergoing illegal abortions, the association said.
</P>
<P>
The FPAN has introduced a fetus protection bill in the Upper
House as a non-governmental bill to deal with the problem.
</P>
<P>
The bill stresses the protection of the reproductive rights of
women and it is believed that the bill will help reduce the
maternal death, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the FPAN has provided free family planning services
to couples in 33 districts and planned to extend the services to
all the 75 districts in the country, the agency added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
