<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cai Duan Dead at 84 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Cai Duan, 84, a member of the
Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), China's highest advisory body,
died of illness on September 15 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Cai, native to central China's Hunan Province, was also a
member of the China Democratic League and a member of the CPPCC
subcommittee on Cultural and Historical Data and Research.
</P>
<P>
Cai Duan was the son of Cai E (1882-1916), a famous patriotic
general in China's modern history.
</P>
<P>
Cai graduated from the History Department at Catholic (Fu Jen)
University in Beijing in 1937, and worked with the foreign affairs
ministry of Kuomintang Government.
</P>
<P>
He worked as an editor with the Beijing-based Guangming Daily
and with the Culture and History Office under the CPPCC after the
founding of new China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
Cai also served as a member of the Sixth and Seventh National
Committee of CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
His remains were cremated on September 21 in Beijing.
</P>
</TEXT>
