<HEADLINE> Guangdong Steps up Technological Cooperation with Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Intensifying scientific and
technological cooperation between Guangdong Province and its
neighboring Hong Kong is now playing an increasingly more
important role in the economic growth of both regions.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong entrepreneurs invested in nearly 80 percent of
Guangdong's 200 top overseas-funded technological enterprises,
which were selected by provincial government organs in charge of
foreign economy and technological development.
</P>
<P>
At the start of their cooperation, Guangdong gathered funding
and Hong Kong provided advanced equipment and technology. Since
the mid-1980s, they have engaged in joint investment and
technological cooperation involving hi-tech enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong focuses on research and production, and Hong Kong
concentrates on further development and marketing of products.
</P>
<P>
In order to strengthen technological exchanges, Guangdong and
Hong Kong have set up an association for the promotion of the
scientific and technological industry, and a research institute in
Shenzhen, China's first Special Economic Zone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
