<HEADLINE> UEFA Urges Revise Crowded International Calendar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The crowded international
calendar must be revised and streamlined to protect the future of
international teams and competitions, European soccer's governing
body UEFA said.
</P>
<P>
UEFA have issued a number of proposals to "guarantee the future
of national representative teams" as the main item for discussion
at a conference on Thursday of its association presidents and
general secretaries here.
</P>
<P>
They included a plan, first put forward by the German Football
Association (DfB), for a reduction in the size of World Cup and
European Championships qualifying groups.
</P>
<P>
UEFA is also proposing the introduction of regular
double-header fixtures to help national coaches have access to
players and for all competitive internationals around the world to
take place on the same day.
</P>
<P>
UEFA have also proposed changes regarding players availability
for World Cup, European qualifiers and friendlies.
</P>
<P>
The European governing body are also proposing players should
be made available by their clubs for a minimum of five friendlies
a year.
</P>
<P>
Among other items for discussion at the conference are the
Collective Selling of TV Rights and professional referees.
</P>
