<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seoul Urges Tokyo, Washington to Keep Transparent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 24 (Xinhua) -- South Korea urged the United
States and Japan Wednesday to maintain transparency in coming up
with any "joint military operation strategies" and "cooperation
plans" under the New Defense Guidelines.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the Foreign Ministry paid attention to the parts of
the new guidelines that call for the observation of the basic format
of the U.S.-Japan security alliance, engagement in activities only for
defensive purpose under the Japanese Constitution and the principle of
denuclearization.
</P>
<P>
It hoped that Tokyo and Washington will continue to closely
consult with Seoul on issues which involve South Korea's
sovereignty in connection with the implementation of the new
defense guidelines which was agreed upon on Tuesday to replace the
1978 guidelines.
</P>
<P>
The new guidelines allow Japanese forces to operate in emergency
situations in surrounding areas in support of American troops,
triggering concerns over the expanded role of the Japanese military
among Asian neighbors, which suffered from Japanese militarism during
and before World War II. 
</P>
</TEXT>
