<HEADLINE> Huge Tumor Removed from Baby Boy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A tumor bigger than a table
tennis paddle has been removed from the facial area of a
five-month-old baby boy in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The tumor, weighing 1,500 grams or one fourth of the baby's
total weight, had grown around his common carotid artery,
hypoglossal nerve and vagus nerve, making the surgery complicated
and dangerous, according to surgeons with the No.9 People's
Hospital of Shanghai, in east China.
</P>
<P>
The baby boy, named Li Lancheng, was born with the tumor, which
at the time of his birth was as large as his head, his parents
said. They said they did not allow him to sleep on his back
for fear he would strangle.
</P>
<P>
Surgeons completely removed the tumor in a six-hour operation
on August 26. Baby Li was discharged and is recovering at home,
according to hospital sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
