<HEADLINE> 11th World Meat Congress Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The 11th World Meat Congress
convened here Tuesday, the first of its kind ever hosted
by the International Meat Secretariat in an Asian country.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing attended the opening ceremony
of the three-day event, which attracted 600 deputies from 35
countries.
</P>
<P>
With a theme of improving the quality of meat products to
ensure customers' satisfaction, participants will discuss issues
ranging from prospects for the international meat trade, the
development of the meat trade in the Asian-Pacific region and the
opportunities for import and export of meat.
</P>
<P>
Participants will also study the economic, legal and
environmental aspects of meat production, processing, technology
and trade, and exchange production experience.
</P>
<P>
In his address at the opening ceremony, the vice premier said
that the congress provides a good opportunity not only for people
from other countries to learn more about China's meat production,
but also for Chinese meat production enterprises to enter the
world market.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Chinese central government has launched a
nationwide "vegetable basket" scheme aiming at improving the
supply of non-staple foodstuffs for urban residents. It has also
worked to develop meat, poultry and egg production, which has
played a positive role in stabilizing prices in the non-staple
food market, said the vice-premier.
</P>
<P>
At present, rural and urban markets are full of a variety of
goods. Per capita availability of meat products, poultry and eggs
has exceeded the world average, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier said that the Chinese government would
continue to support enterprises to expand cooperation with
their overseas partners and jointly explore the international meat
market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
