enshrined in the three Sino-U.S. joint communiques, handle the
question of Taiwan with prudence, and no longer allow this
question to interfere with the progress and growth of
Sino-U.S. relations," said Qian.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes his meeting with Albright could contribute
to the further improvement of relations between the two countries
and create favorable conditions for President Jiang's visit to the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Albright said progress has been made in preparation for the
Chinese President's visit. "We will continue to lay the
basis for a sound and constructive relationship between the United
States and China."
