<DOCNO> XIE19970924.0232 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Artificial Rainfall Helps Relieve Drought in Northwest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Cloud-seeding and other
techniques for making artificial rain have helped to relieve
drought in this arid land of northwest China.
</P>
<P>
Since early this year, Gansu Province has sent 28 planes,
flying a total of more than 30,000 kilometers, to produce 700
million cubic meters of artificial rainfall through a process
known as cloud-seeding, in which chemicals are released into the
clouds to produce rain.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another technique which uses artillery shells to
melt hailstones in the sky, has been used more than 1,000 times,
to prevent crop damage from hail and increase the amount of rain.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, Gansu was hit by a serious drought which covered a
large part of the province and lasted for months. The local
government sent 43 planes for cloud-seeding in the spring, summer
and autumn, and created 890 million cubic meters of rain.
</P>
<P>
In Yongchang County, where the drought had lingered for 75
days, the water supply in the country reservoir was increased by
12 million cubic meters through artificial rainfall.
</P>
<P>
The grain output of the county was rose by eight million kg,
which meant that for each yuan spent in making artificial rain,
grain output volume increased by more than eight million kg.
</P>
<P>
Located in northwest China, Gansu is often plagued by drought
and hailstorms, said Xie Jinnan, director of the province's
meteorological bureau.
</P>
<P>
In the past six years, 51 of the province's 86 counties have
been benefited from the artificial rainfall, which guaranteed the
good harvests in these years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970924.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> University, Business Co-Build Computer School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The prestigious Chinese
University of Science and Technology (CUST) and Legend Group,
China's leading computer hardware manufacturer, have signed an
agreement to co-establish a computer school.
</P>
<P>
The CUST-Legend Computer School, to be located in this capital
of east China's Anhui province, will focus on training management
and technological personnel for the computer industry.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the school will include a personnel
training branch, a research arm, an internship base, and two funds
for scientific research and education.
</P>
<P>
Legend is to invest an initial two million yuan in the school,
and put two million yuan toward the scientific research fund and
200,000 yuan toward the education fund each year.
</P>
<P>
One of the most prestigious universities in China, CUST is
famed for its highly-qualified faculty and strength in scientific
research. Legend group is among the 120 national key enterprise
groups and the largest group company in China's thriving
information industry. Four of its ten vice presidents are CUST
alumni.
</P>
<P>
The cooperative project is expected to greatly improve the
strength of the Chinese University of Science and Technology in
computer and information education.  
</P>
