<HEADLINE> Italy, Germany Sign Agreement on Research Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Italian Education Minister Luigi
Berlinguer and his German counterpart Juergen Ruettgers signed an
agreement in Florence today to further cooperation on research and
education between the two European neighbors.
</P>
<P>
As part of closer collaboration on research between the two
countries, meetings between the heads of Italian and German
research bodies will be held annually, the two ministers said.
</P>
<P>
The German minister arrived in Florence, Italy, earlier in the
day. During their talks, Berlinguer and Ruettgers focused
attention on issues such as the protection of cultural heritage,
university education and language instruction.
</P>
<P>
As technology develops rapidly throughout the world, the
ministers said, bilateral, even multilateral cooperation becomes
increasingly important.
</P>
<P>
Italy and Germany, with their own distinct advantages in
education and research, should work to complement each other in
solving problems, they added. 
</P>
