<DOCNO> XIE19970924.0238 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Fights Iodine Deficiency Disorders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is making efforts to
fight against Iodine Deficiency Disorders (IDD) by implementing
the mechanism for iodization of all salt produced in the country
and making people consume iodized salt.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a three-day National Workshop on Control of IDD in
Myanmar, which began Tuesday, Minister for Health U Saw Tun said
the IDD control program includes production, distribution and
quality assurance of iodized salt, building community awareness of
the IDD problem and availability of iodized salt, The New Light of
Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
He called for further strengthening action plans to achieve
universal iodization of salt by the year 2000 as a sustainable
strategy for the control of IDD in Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is collaborating with United Nations agencies such as
UNDP, WHO and UNICEF in combat against IDD and carrying out
iodized drinking water projects for people in areas where the IDD
problem is considerably great.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is being attended by representatives from UN
agencies and non-governmental organizations, government officials
and private entrepreneurs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
