<HEADLINE> Exports of Uruguayan Wool Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Wool exports in Uruguay
increased 24.5 percent to 84,220 tons by August 31 in the current
collecting season, compared with the same period of last season.
</P>
<P>
According to Uruguay's Secretariat of Wool, out of the total
foreign sales, wool made up 72.9 percent with 61,373 tons, 34.5
percent higher than the figure in 1996.
</P>
