<HEADLINE> Belgium Aganist Soccer Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Belgium plans to crack down
on soccer pitch invasions and crowd violence with new legislation,
interior minister Johan Vande Lanotte said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The new rules means that the fans would to be banned or fined
without a court ruling.
</P>
<P>
Supporters of Belgian soccer clubs Anderlecht, Sint-Truiden
and Antwerp staged pitch invasions and briefly halted games in
three separate matches last weekend.
</P>
<P>
Vande Lanotte said that would change the fans mentality and
their behaviour.
</P>
<P>
Vande Lanotte is currently preparing a bill which is due to be
discussed by the government in the next few weeks and should
become effective from next season. The ministry will send names of
troublemakers to the soccer union on a regular basis. 
