<HEADLINE> Colombia Boosts Banana Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Banana exports
from Colombia amounted to 111.99 million U.S. dollars in the first
quarter of this year, an increase of 7.3 percent over the same
period of 1996, it was reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The Association of Colombian Banana Producers said in a press
release that last year's exports outgrew the 1995 overseas sales
of the product by 21 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Banana exports reached its highest point in January, with the
single-month sales reaching 41.55 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The European Union is one of the biggest markets for Colombian
banana exports, and it bought above 9 million boxes weighing 18.14
kilograms each. 
