<HEADLINE> Maradona to Play Supercup Match in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Diego Maradona will play
for Boca Juniors in Wednesday's South American Supercup match away
to Chilean side Colo Colo, his manager Guillermo Coppola said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The former Argentina captain has played twice in the last week.
But it would be his first game outside Argentina since making the
fifth comeback of his career.
</P>
<P>
Maradona played for 89 minutes in the 2-1 win over San Lorenzo
in the Argentine championship match on Sunday, then turned down on
his threat to make the match his last.
</P>
<P>
He has been provisionally suspended by the Argentine
Football Association after failing a dope test taken after the
match against Argentinos Juniors.
</P>
<P>
But an Argentine court has ruled that he can continue playing
until an investigation into the doping test has been carried
out.
</P>
<P>
Maradona denies taking drugs. 
