<HEADLINE> Bebeto's Dispute with Victoria Turns Bitter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian soccer club
Vitoria Tuesday suspended the wages of the striker Bebeto and
accused him of indiscipline.
</P>
<P>
Club president Paulo Carneiro said Bebeto was in Rio de Janeiro
and refused to return to the club, which is based in the
North-Eastern city of Salvador.
</P>
<P>
The furious club president said that they also thought of
suspending the contract with Bebeto.
</P>
<P>
Bebeto, 33, who help Brazil to the World Cup title in 1994
together with Romario, has 62 full international caps and has
scored 32 goals for Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Last month Bebeto received an offer to rejoin Spain's Deportivo
Coruna, from which he left after the 1995-1996 season. Bebeto said
he was interested in going.
</P>
<P>
However Vitoria turned down Deportivo's offer. Bebeto limped
off injured in the first half of their next game and was jeered by
fans.
</P>
<P>
Bebeto scored eight goals for Vitoria in the Brazilian
championship before his injury. He is still the squad's leading
scorer in the competition.
</P>
<P>
He joined the club at the start of the year after brief spans
with Rio de Janeiro club Flamengo and then with Spanish club
Sevilla. 
</P>
</TEXT>
