<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas-Funded Firms Playing Bigger Role in North Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, in north China, has
over 10,000 foreign-funded enterprises with a total investment of
20 billion US dollars and uses more than five billion US dollars
in overseas funds annually.
</P>
<P>
Five years ago, however, it was less than two billion US
dollars a year.
</P>
<P>
The city has 90 large overseas-funded enterprises with ten
million US dollars in investment each, nearly three times the
figure five years ago. Annual exports of the foreign-funded firms
have risen to two billion US dollars in five years, from only 200
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, 74 enterprises added 365
million US dollars to their projects. The firms are expected to
account for 53.15 percent of Tianjin's total exports this year.
</P>
<P>
Many internationally-known brands are produced in Tianjin, like
Dynasty wines, Otis elevators, Motorola communications equipment,
and Shell oil. Overseas-funded firms are mainly involved in
electronics, engineering, and chemical and medical industries, and
employ more than 200,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 4,000 of the city's overseas-funded firms are in the
Tianjin Economic Development Area in the Binhai New Area, an
integrated development area involved in international trade and
transportation, export industry, and finances.
</P>
<P>
The zone now accounts for 60 percent of the total industrial
output value and export volume in Binhai.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that Tianjin's economic development will
largely depend on the zone in future and the foreign-funded firms
are expected to play an even greater role in the local economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
