<HEADLINE> China's Textile Production Changes Mixedly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China's textile industry
registered a mixed change in output during the January-July period
this year, producing three million tons of yarn and 11.4 billion
meters of cloth, said the latest statistics from State Statistical
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
These two figures represent an increase of 8.5 percent and 11.5
percent, respectively, over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
