<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov downs Former French Open Champions Bruguera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia
blew past former French Open champions Spaniard Sergi Bruguera
with two straight sets at the Grand Slam Cup tennis tournament on
Tuesday in Munich, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Russian Kafelnikov, who won on the Paris clay last year,
crushed Bruguera, who triumphed in the French capital in 1993 and
1994, 6-4, 6-3 in 73 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The quick, synthetic surface of Munich's Olympia Halle gave
Kafelnikov advantage to use his powerful groundstrokes to make the
match a one-side affair.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, who made sure of 250,000 U.S. dollars in prize
money, will face either Briton Greg Rusedski or Australian Todd
Woodbridge for a place in the semi-finals.  
</P>
