<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO Conducts "Dynamic Mix'97" Exercise in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) today launched a three-week multinational
military exercise with Greece's participation after a long absence.
</P>
<P>
The exercise, code-named "Dynamic Mix '97" and coordinated by
NATO's southern flank headquaters, will include three regional
exercises to be taken place in Greece's Macedonia, Thessaly and
the western Peloponnese.
</P>
<P>
Also participated are Belgium, Britain, Germany, Denmark,
Spain, Portugal, Holland, Norway and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The chief of the exercises coordination office at the Greek
armed forces general staff said that the exercise would cover the
entire space of Greece and meet Greece's demands in the current
phase.
</P>
<P>
A U.S. airforce P-3 aircraft taking part in the exercise
skidded off the landing runway and caught fire after its left
wheel broke at Souda airbase in the southern Greek island of Crete
early today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
